# Progressive Disclosure

## Rules

- Layer 1 (always-on): root entry files (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, README.md, 00-overview.mdc) — stay minimal, no background knowledge, routing links only
- Layer 2 (task-time): task contracts, skill files, workflow docs — loaded when executing a specific task
- Layer 3 (reference): goals, architecture, decisions, and other docs/ files — consulted only when needed
- Do not promote layer 3 content into layer 1 files.
- When a layer 1 file grows continuously, routing is failing — move content down, not up.
